                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>On 17 February a daughter, <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1621">Leonarda Catharina Adriana</rs>, had been born to <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_761">Caroline</rs> and <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_760">Willem</rs> van Stockum-Haanebeek.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p>Cf. Rom. 12:17 and 1 Pet. 3:9.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="3" xml:id="note-t-3">
                            

<p>Van Gogh’s sister <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_412">Anna</rs> was planning, after studying French, to go to England to work (FR b2689).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="4" xml:id="note-t-4">
                            

<p>Lange Poten 10 in The Hague, <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_761">Caroline</rs>’s parental home.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="5" xml:id="note-t-5">
                            

<p>Van Gogh had previously encouraged <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_760 bio.xml#_761">Caroline and Willem van Stockum-Haanebeek</rs> to seek contact with the <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_787 bio.xml#_788">Tersteeg family</rs>. <ref xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" target="let012.xml">See letter 12</ref>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
